/|title=Album Review: Dua Lipa – 'Dua Lipa'|website=The Young Folks|date=2017-07-13|accessdate=2020-07-08|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200625174425/https://www.theyoungfolks.com/music/106362/album-review-dua-lipa-dua-lipa/|archive-date=2020-06-25|dead-url=no|last=de la Rosa|first=Manzanares}}</ref>，並參雜了{{tsl|en|dancehall|舞廳 (音樂)|舞廳}}元素<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/dua-lipa-review-2082472|title=Dua Lipa – 'Dua Lipa' Review|website=NME|date=2017-06-01|accessdate=2020-07-08|last=Milton|first=Jamie|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200706222711/https://www.nme.com/reviews/dua-lipa-review-2082472|archive-date=2020-07-06}}</ref>。它是以[[拍號|{{music]]和[[E小調|E小調]]創作，為每分鐘110排，{{tsl|en|chord progression|和弦進程}}為Am–C–Em–D<ref name = "Musicnotes">{{cite web|url=https://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0201439|title=Dua Lipa 'Hotter Than Hell' Sheet Music in E Minor|publisher=Musicnotes.com|accessdate=2020-07-09|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200709174802/https://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0201439|archive-date=2020-07-09|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.umusicpub.com/us/Digital-Music-Library/song/331705/dua-lipa-hotter-than-hell|title=Song Details|publisher=Universal Music Publishing Group|accessdate=2020-07-09|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200709174810/https://www.umusicpub.com/us/Digital-Music-Library/song/331705/dua-lipa-hotter-than-hell|archive-date=2020-07-09}}</ref>。歌曲有著受到[[嘻哈音樂|嘻哈]]影響的{{tsl|en|Song structure#Verse|歌曲架構|正歌}}和[[流行_(音樂類型)|流行]][[副歌|副歌]]<ref name = "Complex"/>。首段正歌中黎波唱道：「you probably still adore me with my hands around your neck」（大意：当我的手在你脖颈间轻轻掠过，你或許還會留戀我）是參考了[[北極潑猴|北極潑猴]]的《{{tsl|en|Favourite Worst Nightmare|Favourite Worst Nightmare|505}}》<ref name = "TSJ">{{cite web|url=https://www.thesinglesjukebox.com/?p=21486|title=Dua Lipa – Hotter Than Hell|work=The Singles Jukebox|date=2016-05-30|accessdate=2020-07-09|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200709202251/https://www.thesinglesjukebox.com/?p=21486|archive-date=2020-07-09}}</ref>。製作由[[马林巴|马林巴]]和[[合成器|合成器]]主導<ref name = "Vulture"/><ref name = "RS Jimmy">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/watch-dua-lipas-steamy-hotter-than-hell-performance-on-fallon-252449/|title=Watch Dua Lipa Perform 'Hotter Than Hell' on 'Fallon'|work=Rolling Stone|date=2016-08-03|accessdate=2020-07-10|last=Reed|first=Ryan|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200710152358/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/watch-dua-lipas-steamy-hotter-than-hell-performance-on-fallon-252449/|archive-date=2020-07-10}}</ref>，並包括{{tsl|en|Steelpan|鋼鼓}}注入合成器、[[管风琴|管风琴]]以及{{tsl|en|Steelpan|鋼鼓|加勒比風格鼓}}創作的[[House_(音樂)|浩室]]、流行和[[熱帶浩室|熱帶浩室]]的節拍<ref name = "TSJ"/><ref name = "Fuse">{{cite web|url=https://www.fuse.tv/2016/05/dua-lipa-hotter-than-hell-video|title=Dua Lipa's 'Hotter Than Hell' Video Will Cure Your Dreary Woes: Watch|date=2016-05-06|accessdate=2020-07-09|last=Gracie|first=Bianca|publisher=Fuse|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200709202217/https://www.fuse.tv/2016/05/dua-lipa-hotter-than-hell-video|archive-date=2020-07-09}}</ref><ref name = "Idolator">{{cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7632658/dua-lipa-hotter-than-hell-video?chrome=1|title=Dua Lipa Is 'Hotter Than Hell' In New Sultry Video: Watch|publisher=Idolator|date=2016-05-06|accessdate=2020-07-09|last=Sonis|first=Rachel|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200709202227/https://www.idolator.com/7632658/dua-lipa-hotter-than-hell-video?chrome=1|archive-date=2020-07-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.readdork.com/reviews/dua-lipa-dua-lipa/|title=Dua Lipa - Dua Lipa|website=Dork|last=Muir|first=Jamie|date=2017-05-30|accessdate=2020-07-09|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200625160514/https://www.readdork.com/reviews/dua-lipa-dua-lipa/|archive-date=2020-06-25}}</ref>。

黎波演唱時使用了沙啞的{{tsl|en|alto|中音 (音域)|中音}}音域，並在[[E_(音名)|E<sub>3</sub>]]到[[D_(音名)|D<sub>5</sub>]]之間<ref name = "TSJ"/><ref name = "Musicnotes"/><ref name = "EW">{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/2016/05/19/allie-x-songs-you-should-be-listening-to/|title=6 songs you should be listening to right now|work=[[娱乐周刊|Entertainment Weekly]]|date=2016-05-19|accessdate=2020-07-10|last=Nolfi|first=Joey|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200710154620/https://ew.com/books/mariah-carey-memoir-all-the-details/|archive-date=2020-07-10}}</ref>。歌曲圍繞[[賦權|賦權]]的主題，而黎波將讓她感到不夠好的男朋友引入歌詞中<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.euphoriazine.com/blog/2017/01/interviews-dua-lipa/|title=Dua Lipa|work=Euphoria Magazine|last=Ersoy|first=Laura|date=2017-01-16|accessdate=2020-07-09|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200709204841/https://www.euphoriazine.com/blog/2017/01/interviews-dua-lipa/|archive-date=2020-07-09}}</ref>。《[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]》的{{tsl|en|Jon Pareles|喬恩·帕雷萊斯}}表示歌詞展示了黎波「（在嘲諷）無法離開她的愛人」，而《[[Spin_(雜誌)|Spin]]》的布倫南·卡利（{{lang|en|Brennan Carley}}）稱它是「關於心痛的描述，當你完全看起來比地獄還火辣時，這是多麼容易去報復對方」<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/05/31/arts/music/dua-lipa-interview.html?_r=0|title=Dua Lipa Was Raised on Pop Bangers. Now She Writes Them|work=[[纽约时报|The New York Times]]|author=Pareles, Jon|date=2017-05-31|accessdate=2020-07-09|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20170601004430/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/05/31/arts/music/dua-lipa-interview.html?_r=0|archive-date=2017-06-01}}</ref><ref name = "Spin MV">{{cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2016/05/dua-lipa-hotter-than-hell-music-video-watch/|title=Dua Lipa's 'Hotter Than Hell' Is One of 2016’s Brightest-Shining Pop Moments|website=Spin|last=Carley|first=Brennan|date=2016-05-06|accessdate=2020-07-09|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20160726182233/http://www.spin.com/2016/05/dua-lipa-hotter-than-hell-music-video-watch/|archive-date=2016-07-26}}</ref>。

==評價==
《打得火熱》獲得主流樂評的讚揚。《[[滾石_(雜誌)|滾石]]》的瑞安·里德（{{lang|en|Ryan Reed}}）稱歌曲「十分火辣」，而《Spin》的丹·魏斯（{{lang|en|Dan Weiss}}）認為它「為她首張同名專輯帶來巨大的希望」<ref name = "Spin"/><ref name = "RS Jimmy"/>。卡利稱它是「流行音樂中明確還保留著生命力和個性的標誌」<ref name = "Spin MV"/>。《[[娛樂周刊|娛樂周刊]]》的喬伊·諾爾菲（{{lang|en|Joey Nolfi}}）表示黎波讓過時的熱帶音樂趨勢聽起來「比任何時候還有清新」，還寫到聽歌時會讓人「（迷失）在棕櫚樹成蔭的流行音樂天堂海岸線上受陽光照射的俱樂部」<ref name = "EW"/>。《[[紐約_(雜誌)|禿鷲]]》的賈斯汀·麥克勞（{{lang|en|Justin McCraw}}）稱歌曲「（充滿）性魅力」以及「充滿慾望和誘惑力」，並推薦要「在酒吧喝完第3杯後回家」時播放<ref name = "Vulture"/>。{{tsl|en|Fuse (TV channel)|Fuse (電視台)|Fuse}}的比安卡·格雷西（{{lang|en|Bianca Gracie}}）稱歌曲的主題「充滿激情」和「信心」，而節拍「極為強烈」<ref name = "Fuse"/>。{{tsl|en|Idolator (website)|Idolator}}的瑞秋·索尼斯（{{lang|en|Rachel Sonis}}）稱它「略帶悲傷和極具感染力」，並認為副歌「十分悶熱」<ref name = "Idolator"/>。

《[[柯夢波丹|柯夢波丹]]》的伊麗莎·湯普森（{{lang|en|Eliza Thompson}}）認為它是黎波的「煙嗓」讓它「提升至[[舞曲|舞曲]]聖歌的等級」<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/music/a58376/best-songs-of-the-week-may-13/|title=8 Songs You Need to Hear This Week|work=[[柯夢波丹|Cosmopolitan]]|last=Thompson|first=Eliza|date=2016-05-13|accessdate=2020-07-10|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200710203628/https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/music/a58376/best-songs-of-the-week-may-13/|archive-date=2020-07-10}}</ref>。《[[新音乐快递|新音乐快递]]》的托馬斯·史密斯（{{lang|en|Thomas Smith}}）稱這首歌曲是「迷人又火辣的流行大熱天，適合魔鬼的迪斯科」<ref name = "NME TS"/>。{{tsl|en|Popjustice|Popjustice}}寫道它是「2016年熱帶音樂風格編織成流行炸曲的最好例子」<ref name = "PopJustice">{{cite web|url=https://www.popjustice.com/articles/the-top-45-singles-of-2016/3/|title=The Top 45 Singles Of 2016|publisher=Popjustice|date=2016-12-19|accessdate=2020-07-10|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200710205037/https://www.popjustice.com/articles/the-top-45-singles-of-2016/3/|archive-date=2020-07-10}}</ref>。《{{tsl|en|Clash (magazine)|音樂碰撞}}》的亞歷克斯·格林（{{lang|en|Alex Green}}）覺得《打得火熱》是首支歌曲讓《杜娃·黎波》「提高要求」，但批評它缺少「真心的能量」<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clashmusic.com/reviews/dua-lipa-dua-lipa|title=Dua Lipa - Dua Lipa|work=Clash|last=Green|first=Alex|date=2017-06-02|accessdate=2020-07-10|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200625160542/https://www.clashmusic.com/reviews/dua-lipa-dua-lipa|archive-date=2020-06-25}}</ref>。《{{tsl|en|The 405 (magazine)|The 405}}》的肖恩·沃德（{{lang|en|Sean Ward}}）將歌曲與[[蕾哈娜|蕾哈娜]]、[[克莉絲汀·阿奎萊拉|-{zh-cn:克里斯蒂娜·阿奎莱拉;zh-hk:基絲甸娜·阿圭莉拉;zh-tw:克莉絲汀·阿奎萊拉}-]]的作品以及[[布蘭妮·斯皮爾斯|布蘭妮·斯皮爾斯]]的《[[再危險...我也要|再危險...我也要]]》作比較<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thefourohfive.com/music/review/review-the-highly-anticipated-self-titled-debut-album-from-dua-lipa-makes-good-on-all-the-hype-149|title=Album Review: Dua Lipa - Dua Lipa|work=The 405|last=Ward|first=Sean|date=2017-06-05|accessdate=2020-07-10|dead-url=yes|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190529084846/https://www.thefourohfive.com/music/review/review-the-highly-anticipated-self-titled-debut-album-from-dua-lipa-makes-good-on-all-the-hype-149|archive-date=2019-05-29}}</ref>。《{{tsl|en|musicOMH|musicOMH}}》的本·霍格伍德（{{lang|en|Ben Hogwood}}）覺得《打得火熱》起初會覺得是「令人激動」的歌曲，但表明在重複聆聽後會變得比較「冷淡」<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.musicomh.com/reviews/albums/dua-lipa-dua-lipa|title=Dua Lipa – Dua Lipa|work=musicOMH|last=Hogwood|first=Ben|date=2017-06-02|accessdate=2020-07-10|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200625173758/https://www.musicomh.com/reviews/albums/dua-lipa-dua-lipa|archive-date=2020-06-25}}</ref>。《{{tsl|en|The Line of Best Fit|The Line of Best Fit}}》的克萊爾·比德爾斯（{{lang|en|Claire Biddles}}）表明黎波在歌曲中懷有「無與倫比的性愛之神」<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/reviews/albums/dua-lipa-dua-lipa|title=Dua Lipa finds conviction in all aspects of her pop star personality|work=The Line of Best Fit|last=Biddles|first=Claire|date=2017-06-05|accessdate=2020-07-10|dead-url=yes|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200625173154/https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/reviews/albums/dua-lipa-dua-lipa|archive-date=2020-06-25}}</ref>。《[[衛報|衛報]]》的漢娜·J·戴維斯（{{lang|en|Hannah J Davies}}）讚賞這首歌曲「聽起來（不）太故意追求潮流」<ref name = "The Guardian"/>。2020年4月，《{{tsl|en|Glamour (magazine)|魅力 (雜誌)|魅力}}》的克里斯托弗·羅莎（{{lang|en|Christopher Rosa}}）將《打得火熱》排在黎波第9最好的歌曲，並稱其「性感又火辣」<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.glamour.com/story/dua-lipa-10-best-and-worst-songs-of-all-time|title=Dua Lipa's 10 Best (and Worst) Songs of All Time|work=Glamour|date=2020-04-13|accessdate=2020-07-10|last=Rosa|first=Christopher|dead-url=yes|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200626025856/https://www.glamour.com/story/dua-lipa-10-best-and-worst-songs-of-all-time|archive-date=2020-06-26}}</ref>。

